ocumentation, it could conflate it with general transaction concepts, which would be misleading. So this is the main gap I've identified in the knowledge file.\n\nLet me verify the messaging section structure one more time. The source document has a parent header for メッセージング処理 that covers both receiving and sending operations, but the knowledge file splits this into s5 for receiving and s6 for sending, which is a reasonable way to organize it.\n\nLooking at the index hints for each section, s5 focuses on receiving-related terms like 同期応答メッセージ受信 and 受信キュー, while s6 emphasizes sending operations with terms like 同期応答メッセージ送信 and 要求電文アサート. The distinction is clear enough to differentiate between them.\n\nI notice s6's hints don't explicitly include 受信キュー even though the source material mentions it, but since that's not a PascalCase class name, annotation, or exception type, it wouldn't qualify as a V4 finding. The knowledge file looks structurally sound overall, though there's a minor hint completeness issue I should note.\n\nThe key finding is that s2 omits the important caveat that \"取引\" is a book-specific definition, not a general transaction concept. This matters because an AI using this knowledge file could easily conflate Nablarch's specialized meaning with standard transaction terminology. I should flag this as an omission finding and include the source evidence from the footnote.\n\nLooking at the overall structure, s2 appropriately consolidates three related overview subsections (クラス, リクエスト, 取引) into one knowledge section, so that's not a structural issue. I think that covers my findings—just the one minor omission about the 取引 definition caveat.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":26066,"cache_read_input_tokens":29807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":26066,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":